10 February 2017The International Cooperation, Trade and Security Cluster chaired by Minister Edna Molewa will brief media on the implementation of the Cluster programme of action for the year, following the 2017 State of the Nation Address. Minister Molewa will be supported by the Co-Chairperson Minister Maite Nkoana-Mashabane and members of the Cluster.The briefing will also outline progress that has been made and future plans to achieve the National Development Plan Vision 2030.Members of the media are invited as follows:Date: Sunday, 12 February 2017 Venue: Imbizo Media Centre, Ground Floor, 120 Plein Street, Parliament: Cape Town. Time: 09h00There will be a video link to GCIS Media Centre, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street: PretoriaNB: Kindly confirm attendance by e-mail to: Andile Duka (Cape Town) E-mail: Andiled@gcis.gov.za Cell: 071 154 5619Themba Thobela (Pretoria) E-mail: Themba@gcis.gov.za Cell: 076 0956 555Enquiries: Albi Modise Cell: 083 490 2871Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) on behalf of the International Cooperation, Trade and Security Cluster